---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Six Digits"
	description="Six Digits is a blog for tech professionals and fresh graduates navigating the AI era."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-10')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>Six Digits</strong> exists because the AI conversation in tech is broken in two directions at once.
	</p>

	<p>
		On one side, experienced engineers are being told AI will replace them — generating anxiety
		without clarity. On the other, fresh graduates are entering a job market where entry-level hiring
		has collapsed 73% year-over-year, with no roadmap for what to do about it.
	</p>

	<p>
		Both groups need the same thing: a clear-eyed framework for what's actually changing, what
		remains human, and how to position yourself on the right side of the shift.
	</p>

	<h2>What This Blog Is For</h2>

	<p>
		Six Digits is for two audiences:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Tech professionals struggling with AI</strong> — senior and mid-level engineers,
			data engineers, and developers trying to understand what their job looks like in an
			AI-native world and how to stay valuable.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Fresh graduates entering the AI era</strong> — new CS grads, bootcamp alumni,
			and career switchers who want to learn how to use AI as a force multiplier rather than
			competing against it as a substitute.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>What We Cover</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>How AI is reshaping the anatomy of software engineering work</li>
		<li>Which skills are becoming more valuable and which are being automated away</li>
		<li>Practical workflows for working with AI coding tools effectively</li>
		<li>Career strategy for engineers at every level in the AI era</li>
		<li>Deep dives into frameworks for thinking about software, systems, and judgment</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>The Name</h2>

	<p>
		Six digits — as in, a six-figure career. The name is a nod to the goal that brings most people
		into tech: building a career with real earning power. AI changes how you get there, not whether
		you can.
	</p>

	<h2>Who Writes This</h2>

	<p>
		This blog is written by a software engineer and technologist obsessed with how AI is restructuring
		the profession — using frameworks like Problem Anatomy and Jobs to Be Done to cut through the noise
		and find what actually matters for building a durable career in tech.
	</p>
</Layout>
